name: Rich Wissmueller
about:
Category Manager, Global Logistics Procurement
Freight Payment, Parcel, Air Forwarding
Xylem Inc.

Formerly:
Independent Supply Chain Consultant, Charlton Enterprises, LLC

Project Manager at EEMCM Extended Enterprise Material Cost Management (privately-held; Google 'Kenneth P. Horn, EDI"). Mapping a major non-automotive OEM Electronic Data Interchange (EDI) network and processes to improve efficiencies, both inbound parts and outbound product applications/transactions.

Faurecia Automotive Seating Production Control & Logistics (PC&L) Lead for Nissan programs. Responsible for complete supply chain management: supplier transportation routings (JIT), returnable container design & purchasing, in-plant warehouse to line-side feed.

Lear dealt with managing supply disruptions from distressed suppliers due to the Japanese tsunami, earthquake, and nuclear reactor fallout (short-term assignment).

Chrysler Supply Chain experience, including plant production and material control (Pick & Pack, truck & rail docks); corporate Production Control JIT, Logistics, strategies, plant analyst, buyer of inbound rail, truck, expedite, LTL, heavy haul, trailer switching, and local cartage. Managed the Fuel Adjustment Process (FAP); carrier quotes & contracts.

Specialties: Using IT solutions to streamline processes and create efficiencies / cost savings / administrative reductions and eliminate redundancies.

Some of the biggest users of our service are in the auto, aero and electronics industries.

campaign: I am selling software quality assurance and testing as a consulting service to manufacturing companies that use Teamcenter as their PLM tool.  We have been Siemens testing partner for Teamcenter since 2005, and test the product pre release for any new updates.  Our ideal candidates are very large enterprises that are looking to modernize and go through more frequent upgrades.  Some of the biggest users of our service are in the auto, aero and electronics industries.

about:
I take pride in the development of the individuals on the team. I have a strong belief in the correlation between team growth and organizational growth and have a proven track record in process formulation that efficiently supports sales activities while meeting the highest operational standards. Results do not always justify the method, but should always be considered during the process, a KPI that goes un-measured will remain un-changed.

I have acquired over 20 years of experience working in various industries and devoting many years within the Information Technology field, there's a lot of perspective, discipline, and value that I can bring to the table.

Recently, I had leveraged those experiences as a solutions project manager consultant to work with clients across various industries (including medical, finance, insurance, government, utility, consumer, and manufacturing) to solve their immediate challenges and achieve their desired business and IT strategic goals...

campaign: I am selling software quality assurance and testing as a consulting service to manufacturing companies that use Teamcenter as their PLM tool.  We have been Siemens testing partner for Teamcenter since 2005, and test the product pre release for any new updates.  Our ideal candidates are very large enterprises that are looking to modernize and go through more frequent upgrades.  Some of the biggest users of our service are in the auto, aero and electronics industries.

about:
Global Operations Management Professional with 20+ years of experience in delivering continuous organizational improvements for corporate leaders within phosphate and aerospace industries. Proven track record of demonstrated metric attainment, supplier quality/development, superior employee interactions, and operational cost savings.

Previously, I was Project Manager at United Technologies Corporation – Aviation Systems, where I managed multiple global and domestic projects. The projects required process, product transfers to multiple regions in India, Germany and the USA.

Competencies: Strategic Analysis/Project Planning, Root Cause Corrective Action, Domestic/International Supplier Quality/Development, Quality Control: Welding, Change Management, First Article Build and Certification, Production Integration, Lean Six Sigma/Continuous Improvement, Cross-Functional Team Leadership

about:
Sr. Business Development Manager, committed to providing commercial level contract furniture solutions.

I have been working in the Contract furniture industry for over 15 years. Originally in the NYC metro area.
I worked as a BDM in both capacities as a Dealer Rep and as a Manufacturer Rep. I love the furniture industry, as I am passionate about space planning and providing state of the art furniture and design solutions for my customers.

Over the past 7 years with Workspace Interiors and our exceptional team of Designers and Project Managers, I have had the privilege to win many modern learning ReDesigns in School Districts throughout my region. I have also enjoyed the ability to drive a nationwide Furniture Standards program that spans the USA north, south, east and west. I enjoy the challenge of coordinating large capital projects and we definitely have the team to get it done.

I am centrally located in Stamford, Ct and work the New England region and NY Metro Area to include Long Island and Westchester county. It's a beautiful region with a wide variety of Odp Accts in the Healthcare, Corporate and Education Markets.

It takes a village to coordinate building & interiors solutions and I love the collaboration and commitment. We offer: Design services, Project management, Over 200 furniture manufacturers, Nationwide Furniture Standards, Furniture ReDesigns, ReManufacturing, Decommissioning, Work from Home Solutions and more.

Committed to: Excellence, Customer Service, Collaboration and Sustainability.

name: Alex Schwartzman
position: F-22 Senior Program Manager at Boeing
about: Alex Schwartzman manages a team of project managers executing sustainment for the Air Force premier fighter fleet. Performs program management with focus on reliability, availability, maintainability programs (RAMP) as well as proposal execution. The team ensures platform needs are covered by segmenting the systems and structures to unify activity in those areas. Previous positions held were as Manager of Defense Logistics Agency and F-15 Singapore Performance Based Logistics Supply Chains, Manager of Spares Order Management of the Defense Logistics Agency and Large Aircraft Spares and Engineering program requirements. Additionally, he was a Supply Chain Specialist in Repair Order Management and was the Team Lead for International, Navy, and Air Force aircraft teams. Prior to his Boeing career, he was enlisted in the Air Force where he was a Flying Crew Chief on the E-4B, a modified Boeing 747-200. Alex is a graduate of Embry Riddle Aeronautical University, where he earned a BS in Professional Aeronautics with emphasis in Management and Safety. He also has a Masters of Business Administration in Aviation from Embry Riddle Aeronautical University.

campaign: I am selling software quality assurance and testing as a consulting service to manufacturing companies that use Teamcenter as their PLM tool.  We have been Siemens testing partner for Teamcenter since 2005, and test the product pre release for any new updates.  Our ideal candidates are very large enterprises that are looking to modernize and go through more frequent upgrades.  Some of the biggest users of our service are in the auto, aero and electronics industries.
name: Matthew Boley
about:
Public Assistance (PA) Emergency Management:
Team Lead and Technical Lead with extensive disaster-related experience leading and managing PA teams providing grants management assistance services in support of declared national disasters. From 06/2018 to 12/2019, led and supervised a 9-person team of professionals (architects, engineers) providing grants management services under an FLUOR/ATCS contract in support of FEMA Disaster DR-4339-PR, in the aftermath of the Hurricane Maria disaster in Puerto Rico. Provided advice and guidance to Task Force Leads (TFLs), FEMA leadership, University leadership and administration, management at ATCS & FLUOR, among others. Given the rapidly developing crisis, completed multiple critical leadership functions, including Team Lead (40 professionals), Technical Lead (15 professionals), Primary Program Delivery Manager (PDMG), Site Inspector, and Quality Control Technician. Experienced with FEMA Public Assistance (PA) policies and procedures, the PA Grants Management (National Model) process and systems, and the development of Damage Description and Dimensions (DDDs) and Scopes of Work (SOWs). Co-coordinated and supported implementation of disaster recovery services. During 2017, Individual Assistance (IA) Disaster Housing Inspector for FEMA Disaster DR-4337, in the aftermath of Hurricane Irma, in Tampa Florida and surrounding areas. Leverages excellent leadership, management, communications, problem solving, and interpersonal skills to respond to the nation’s most significant challenges.

Infectious Disease (Virus/Bacteria)/Toxins/BioDefense:
Lead Biologist at the ATCC for the BEIR contract performing and leading infectious disease and biological defense studies, experiments, research, and product development (2005 to 2015). Possesses PhD-level education in both science and public policy. Represented ATCC and the biodefense contract on many occasions at scientific conferences interacting with scientists, vendors, and clients. Highly experienced in working directly with biodefense select agents and infectious disease & toxins in specialized, high-containment laboratories. Designed and executed many and experiments which led to various discoveries, assays, and publications/presentations. Led or co-developed major infectious disease and biological toxins product development projects.

Other:
Certified Construction Project Manager, Class A Contractor, and entrepreneur.

*ATCS team lead in Puerto Rico.
*Team lead for Puerto Rico Department of Education (PRDE), FEMA Education Sector, containing approximately 35 architects and engineers.
*Technical lead for Private Non-profit Education Sector division.
*Initiated and co-developed a computer program that accelerated Damage Description and Dimensions (DDD), Scope of Work (SOW), and cost estimate time to completion. This Excel-based program completed all three simultaneously and contained integrated RS Means construction estimating software costing. I led uploading it to an iPad and integrated it into site inspections. With the software, site inspection to final, PW-ready documents could be completed in approximately four days.
*Developed internal training program for PRDE approximately 70 Project Specialists.
*Spearheaded the technical transfer of team structure, methods, and computer software from the PRDE division to the PNP division.
*Spearheaded PRDE Activities Committee.
*Directly supported PRDE and PNP TFLs on a variety of projects, processes, and issues.
*Key team member of PRDE team that moved a Project Worksheet (PW) for 64 schools through to signature.
*Worked directly with the Puerto Rico Secretary of Education's liaison on a variety of projects including obtaining signatures for the 64 school PW.
*Worked directly with COR3 (Recipient) to discuss and negotiate details of multiple PWs for obtaining signature from the State of Puerto Rico.

campaign: I am selling software quality assurance and testing as a consulting service to manufacturing companies that use Teamcenter as their PLM tool.  We have been Siemens testing partner for Teamcenter since 2005, and test the product pre release for any new updates.  Our ideal candidates are very large enterprises that are looking to modernize and go through more frequent upgrades.  Some of the biggest users of our service are in the auto, aero and electronics industries.
name: Mark Weddington
about:
LA-based art director/graphic designer with a strong background in design, marketing and branding in both print and digital realms.

Agency work includes clients ranging from major movie studios and Fortune 500 companies to small businesses. Adept in collaborating both directly with clients on a one-to-one basis as Creative Director and managing junior designers, as well as working as part of a team with project managers, creative directors, art directors and/or programmers.

Freelance work includes music-oriented independent projects for clients across the country and overseas. Culturally sensitive with well-rounded aesthetic sensibilities and wide variety of client interaction experience.

Online portfolio: www.behance.net/soulmarcosa

Specialties:
• Digital advertising and social media campaigns for the entertainment industry.
• Branding, marketing, motion graphics, A/V editing and logo design.
• Print design (advertising, brochures, posters, etc.).
• Website, eCommerce & UI design.
• Excellent proficiency in Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign, Dreamweaver and Quark Xpress.
• Intermediate proficiency in After Effects, Wordpress, HTML, CSS, Mailchimp, Campaign Monitor, and Constant Contact.
• Experienced in integration of PHP, Jquery, Ajax, Javascript and Miva.
• Specialist in design for music, film and Black, Latino and Indian markets.

recommendations: ["“I had the privilege of working with Orlando on an aircraft development program where he had the Project Engineering responsibility for the development of a new Gulfstream interior. Orlando is thorough, knowledgeable, and reliable in his work. I could always depend on him to follow through on whatever I asked of him. He was instrumental in developing technical plans that met overall needs and objectives as well as executing those plans and holding owners accountable for their deliverables. On top of his skillset and dependability, he brings a very positive attitude to work and is a joy to work besides! ” Show less","“Over the past five years, I have had the opportunity to work closely with Orlando. He is an experienced Aerospace and Defense Engineer who was responsible for managing the technical aspects of the aerospace projects that were being manufactured at numerous Flex sites in the USA and Mexico. He worked with the site’s Engineering, Process, Methods and Operations teams to develop and implement manufacturing processes and procedures that utilized continuous improvement and lean manufacturing techniques which resulted in reductions in costs and improvements in delivered customer quality. He collaborated closely with our customer’s engineering teams to insure that Engineering Change Orders were clear and that they were incorporated into Flex’s Change Control Process to support the required effectivity. Orlando also developed metrics to track the transition, installation and checkout of customer supplied complex test equipment and software. I consider Orlando to be many things including a hard-working professional, a dedicated leader, a team mentor and a good friend. I highly recommend him since he would make a great addition to any team.” Show less"]

name: James L Freimuth, Jr
about:
Jim is a dedicated internet marketing entrepreneur, and operates a marketing/consulting business known as The JLMars OMNI Enterprise. Jim is involved in the day to day marketing of a wide array of consumer products to Preferred Customers via the Market America’s UnFranchise Business Development Program. Jim also provides collaborative patent development assistance to inspiring entrepreneurs as a freelancer.

Jim has 15 years experience as a Project Manager/Systems Engineer with in high-tech military product design and manufacturing in the field of Anti-Submarine Warfare (ASW) undersea acoustic technology, advanced aero structures, naval missile launchers, advanced autonomous array sonobuoy, composite armor vehicles, waste remediation, advanced composite technology, and most recently Inertial Confinement Fusion (ICF) thermonuclear research collaboration with the DOD/DOE.

At the University of Rochester LLE, Jim focused on the implementation of concurrent engineering strategies within a dedicated project matrix organization. At Martin Marietta Aero & Naval Systems, Jim developed a host of various concurrent engineering and total quality management (CE/TQM) implementation strategies as a member of the technical operations (Tech Ops) department. Other accomplishments include coordinating technical specifications for sophisticated military systems within a large group of engineering professionals at various US Naval Laboratories. Assignments in and around Washington DC have encompassed mechanical engineering, detailed technical analysis, system engineering, installation planning, database development, logistics, configuration management, cost analysis, test evaluation, resource planning, project management, operational certification testing, technical management and coordinating government acquisition projects. Jim is able to manage a wide variety of tasks including people, and leverage a wide variety of digital media for engineering, design and management.

Specialties: Dedicated to building successful enterprises as an Independent Entrepreneur.

campaign: I am selling software quality assurance and testing as a consulting service to manufacturing companies that use Teamcenter as their PLM tool.  We have been Siemens testing partner for Teamcenter since 2005, and test the product pre release for any new updates.  Our ideal candidates are very large enterprises that are looking to modernize and go through more frequent upgrades.  Some of the biggest users of our service are in the auto, aero and electronics industries.
